This is README file for Algorithm PA#1
Author: Hao-Chien Lin, B04901162
Date: March/20/2018
=====
SYNOPSIS:

mysort -[IS|MS|HS] <input_file_name> <output_file_name>

This program supports three different sorting methods: insertion sort, merge sort and heap sort.
=====
DIRECTORY:

bin/	  executable binary
doc/	  reports
inputs/   input data (unsorted)
outputs/  output result (sorted)
lib/	  library
src/ 	  source C++ codes
utility/  checker
======
HOW TO COMPILE:

Then compile the demo, simply follow the following steps
	make
======
HOW TO RUN:

	cd bin/
	./bin/NTU_sort ¡V[IS|MS|HS] <input_file_name> <output_file_name>
	For example,
	./bin/NTU_sort ¡VMS inputs/1000.ac.in outputs/1000.ac.out
======
HOW TO VERIFY RESULT

    cd utility/
    ./PA1_Result_Checker <result_file_name>
	For example,
	./PA1_Result_Checker ../output/5.ac.out

OTHER NOTICE:
The main sorting files located in src/ are the following: main.cpp, sort_tool.cpp, and sort_tool.h. main.cpp does file-io to input and output data. The header file contains all the function and variable definitions of sort_tool.cpp. sort_tool.cpp contains the code for insertion, merge, and heap sort.
